<h1 id="example-conjugation">Example Conjugation</h1>
<p>An example input to the conjugator is ‚ÄúINDEP+POS+PAST+onjise+4SG‚Äù. The tags carry the following grammatical information:</p>
<ul>
  <li>+3SG: 3rd person plural</li>
  <li>+3PL: 3rd person plural</li>
  <li>+4SG: 4th person singular</li>
  <li>+3PL: 4th person plural</li>
</ul>

<p>The conjugated verb form returned by the API is ‚Äúgii-onijiseni‚Äù. The following graph shows the underlying finite state transducer.</p>

<p><img src="/portfolio/img/posts/ojibwe-verb-conjugator/vii-fst.jpeg" alt="vii-fst" /></p>

<h1 id="redesigned-interface">Redesigned Interface</h1>
<p>The redesigned interface calls our API with conjugation parameters and verb stem and populate the results with conjugated forms.</p>

